## What You Need
  * Cisco Packet Tracer (https://www.netacad.com/courses/getting-started-cisco-packet-tracer?courseLang=en-US)
  * The file _project topology.pkt_
## Step 1: Open
  * Open packet tracer
  * File -> Open and select _project topology.pkt_
  * Togole Realtime mode (bottom-right corner) to run the network live
  * Wait 30 seconds for boot up and the links to turn green
## Step 2: Check PCs IP address
  * Click any PC
  * Desktop -> Command prompt
  * Type: ipconfig
  * An IP address will match the VLAN (example - PC0: 192.168.30.x)
## Step 3: Ping PC to a different VLAN
  * In the same command prompt- ping 192.168.50.10
## Step 4: Test Web Server
  * Same PC, Desktop -> Web Browser
  * Type: https://webserver.local
## Step 5: Test Internet Connection
  * Back to command prompt- ping 200.100.100.1

  
